description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Team Administrator &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location – Mental Health Liaison Team, Gloucester Royal Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - £19,737 - £21,142&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: 37.5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mental Health Liaison Services provide a dedicated mental health service within the busy acute hospital setting across Gloucestershire (Gloucestershire Royal and Cheltenham General Hospitals). We have the opportunity to recruit a motivated and professional administrator to work closely with the team in a supportive capacity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The administrator is a core member of the team, with a valued and respected role and without whom the team would not function effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide high level confidential administrative support to a team including Consultant Psychiatrists, Mental Health Liaison Practitioners and the Lead Nurse. You will be expected to work as part of a wider admin team in delivering an effective service, assisting managers and staff across the Trust to ensure that services meet operational needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, the successful candidate will manage their own workload on a day to day basis and act independently to action and prioritise work to meet deadlines. Key responsibilities will include administrating meetings, provide excellent diary management skills and ensuring efficient systems and processes are in place to effectively support the team as a whole. Taking formal minutes and ensuring all relevant papers are available, occasional travel to other venues to take minutes and supporting in the processes to recruit staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent customer service skills are essential as you will be communicating with internal and external professionals and organisation skills and being proactive in showing initiative in planning and prioritising own workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an individual with experience of working as a team administrator at with strong teamwork skills and the ability to maintain a calm, positive and flexible approach to your work, we would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 20/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shortlisting date: 01/12/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff, the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
